When approving a 2-1-1 service provider, 2-1-1 Maryland shall consider:
The ability of the proposed 2-1-1 service provider to meet the national 2-1-1 standards recommended by:
The Alliance of Information and Referral Systems and adopted by the National 2-1-1 Collaborative; or
An equivalent entity;
The financial stability of the proposed 2-1-1 service provider;
Any community support for the proposed 2-1-1 service provider;
Any experience that the proposed 2-1-1 service provider has with other information and referral services;
The degree to which the county in which the proposed call center is to be located has dedicated substantial resources to the establishment of a single telephone source for non-emergency inquiries regarding county services; and
Any other criteria that 2-1-1 Maryland considers appropriate.
